  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Nutritional status in patients with cirrhosis has been shown to have a direct influence on
      the prognosis of these patients, it is related to higher mortality and it has been linked to
      the developement and perpetuation of certain complications such as hepatic encephalopathy,
      ascites and spontaneous bacterial peritonitis.

      Despite the importance of nutritional status in this patients, most of the methods for its
      assessment are still not completely reliable or not easily accessible; therefore, evaluating
      nutritional status in the daily clinical practice is still a complex task.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
